。他去世于1432年在英国英格兰爾埃爾頓享年83岁。"},"hr":{"ABT 1350–1432":"oko 1350.–1432.","1357–1461":"1357–1461","1379–1461":"1379.–1461","1350–1432":"1350–1432.","ABT 1350":"oko 1350.","1379":"1379.","1357":"1357","1432":"1432.","1376":"1376.","1461":"1461","1350":"1350","Elton, Cheshire, England":"Elton, Cheshire, Engleska, United Kingdom","Gwarnack, Cornwall, England":"Cornwall, Engleska, United Kingdom","Woolstone Manor, Bude, Cornwall, England":"Woolstone, Berkshire, England","Devon, England":"Devon, Engleska, United Kingdom"},"cs":{"ABT 1350–1432":"okolo 1350–1432","1357–1461":"1357–1461","1379–1461":"1379–1461","1350–1432":"1350–1432","ABT 1350":"okolo 1350","1379":"1379","1357":"1357","1432":"1432","1376":"1376","1461":"1461","1350":"1350","Elton, Cheshire, England":"Elton, Cheshire, Anglie, United Kingdom","Gwarnack, Cornwall, England":"Cornwall, Anglie, United Kingdom","Woolstone Manor, Bude, Cornwall, England":"Woolstone, Berkshire, Anglie","Devon, England":"Devon, Anglie, United Kingdom"},"da":{"ABT 1350–1432":"omkring 1350–1432","1357–1461":"1357–1461","1379–1461":"1379–1461","1350–1432":"1350–1432","ABT 1350":"omkring 1350","1379":"1379","1357":"1357","1432":"1432","1376":"1376","1461":"1461","1350":"1350","Elton, Cheshire, England":"Elton, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom","Gwarnack, Cornwall, England":"Cornwall, England, United Kingdom","Woolstone Manor, Bude, Cornwall, England":"Woolstone, Berkshire, England","Devon, England":"Devon, England, United Kingdom"},"nl":{"ABT 1350–1432":"circa 1350–1432","1357–1461":"1357–1461","1379–1461":"1379–1461","1350–1432":"1350–1432","ABT 1350":"circa 1350","1379":"1379","1357":"1357","1432":"1432","1376":"1376","1461":"1461","1350":"1350","Elton, Cheshire, England":"Elton, Cheshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Gwarnack, Cornwall, England":"Cornwall, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Woolstone Manor, Bude, Cornwall, England":"Woolstone, Berkshire, England","Devon, England":"Devon, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"ABT 1350–1432":"about 1350–1432","1357–1461":"1357–1461","1379–1461":"1379–1461","1350–1432":"1350–1432","ABT 1350":"about 1350","1379":"1379","1357":"1357","1432":"1432","1376":"1376","1461":"1461","1350":"1350","Elton, Cheshire, England":"Elton, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom","Gwarnack, Cornwall, England":"Cornwall, England, United Kingdom","Woolstone Manor, Bude, Cornwall, England":"Woolstone, Berkshire, England","Devon, England":"Devon, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Beville","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (Middlesex and Surrey; of Norman origin): variant of   Bovill  . Derivation from Beuville (Calvados) is also possible, though unproven.","French (also <b>Béville</b>): habitational name from Béville (Moselle) or Béville-le-Comte (Eure-et-Loir), or a variant of <b>Beuville</b>, a habitational name from Beuville (Calvados). The surname <i>Béville</i> is rare in France."],"variants":[{"name":"Bevill","meanings":["English (of Norman origin): variant of   Beville  ."]},{"name":"Bovill","meanings":["English (of Norman origin): habitational name from any of several places in Normandy whose medieval forms share a similar range of variants, such as Bouville (Seine-Maritime), any of several places called Biéville (Calvados, Manche) or Biville (Manche, Seine-Maritime), Beuzeville-la-Giffard (Seine-Maritime), Boiville (Orne), and perhaps Boudeville (Seine-Maritime). See also   Boswell   and   Beville  ."]}]},{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Contracted form of Old French <i>Jo(h)anne</i>, from Latin <i>Io(h)anna</i> (  see  Joanna  ). In England this was the usual feminine form of   John   from the Middle English period onwards and was extremely popular, but in the 16th and 17th centuries it steadily lost ground to   Jane .  It was strongly revived in the first part of the 20th century, partly under the influence of  George Bernard Shaw's  play St Joan (  1923 ), based on the life of  Joan of Arc  (  1412–31 ). Claiming to be guided by the voices of the saints, she persuaded the French dauphin to defy the occupying English forces and have himself crowned, and she led the French army that raised the siege of Orleans in  1429 . The following year she was captured by the Burgundians and sold to the English, and a year later she was burned at the stake for witchcraft at the age of 18 or 19. Her story has captured the imagination of many writers, and she is variously portrayed as a national and political hero, a model of apolitical straightforwardness and honesty, and a religious heroine. She was canonized in  1920 . More recent influences have included the American film actress  Joan Crawford  (  1908–77 , born  Lucille le Sueur ), the British actress  Joan Collins  (  b. 1933 ), the American comedienne  Joan Rivers  (  b. 1933 ), and the West Indian pop singer  Joan Armatrading  (  b. 1950 )."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Sir John Beville Sheriff of Cornwall was born about 1350, in Cornwall, England, United Kingdom. He married Margaret De Collaton 1 Wife in 1376, in Devon, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. He died in 1432, in Elton, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 83."},"et":{"ABT 1350–1432":"umbes 1350–1432","1357–1461":"1357–1461","1379–1461":"1379–1461","1350–1432":"1350–1432","ABT 1350":"umbes 1350","1379":"1379","1357":"1357","1432":"1432","1376":"1376","1461":"1461","1350":"1350","Elton, Cheshire, England":"Elton, Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Gwarnack, Cornwall, England":"Cornwall, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Woolstone Manor, Bude, Cornwall, England":"Woolstone, Berkshire, England","Devon, England":"Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"ABT 1350–1432":"noin 1350–1432","1357–1461":"1357–1461","1379–1461":"1379–1461","1350–1432":"1350–1432","ABT 1350":"noin 1350","137